  "decision_conditions": [
    "&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:11pt&quot;&gt;The scale&amp;nbsp;siting and design of the&amp;nbsp;proposed Double Storey side extension fails to respect the character and appearance of Babington Road and the Becontree Estate. The part chamferred roof is of an incongruent design and would have a detrimental affect on the external appearance of the dwellinghouse and the streetscene. Furthermore, Hipped roof&#x27;s with a common ridge height is a common characteristic of Babington Road and the Becontree Estate. The addition of a Double Storey Side Extension with a lower Ridge height compared to neighbouring properties would not have regard to the form and function of the surrounding area. Furthermore, due to scale of the proposed double storey side extension, it would close off the corner gap between the junction of Babington Road and Bowes Road. Therefore, the proposal fails to comply with:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;- National Planning Policy Framework (MHCLG, February 2019);&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;- Policies 7.1, 7.4 and 7.6 of The London Plan (March 2016);&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;- Policy D4 of the Draft London Plan Intended to Publish (December 2019);&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;- Policies CP2 and CP3 of the LDF Core Strategy (July 2010);&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;- Policies BP2, BP8 and BP11 of the LDF Borough Wide Development Plan Policies DPD (March 2011);&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;- The Residential Extensions and Alterations Supplementary Planning Document (February 2012);&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;- Policies SP2, SP4, DMD1, and DMD6 of the Draft Local Plan (Regulation 19 Consultation version, October 2020).&lt;/div&gt;"
